<subSubSection id="A7CC2DBDFFCCFFE6FF6BFA34FC8AFEC3" lastPageId="23" lastPageNumber="298" pageId="22" pageNumber="297" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="EF697E36FFCCFFE6FF6BFA34FEDAFEA3" blockId="22.[151,1127,1490,1577]" lastBlockId="23.[113,1089,220,403]" lastPageId="23" lastPageNumber="298" pageId="22" pageNumber="297">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFCCFFE7FF6BFA34FEB8FA59" bold="true" box="[151,262,1490,1513]" pageId="22" pageNumber="297">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFCCFFE7FEF6FA34FE04FA59" author="BOHEMAN" box="[266,442,1490,1513]" firstAuthor="BOHEMAN" pageId="22" pageNumber="297" refId="ref47955" refString="BOHEMAN C. H. 1855: Monographia Cassididarum. Tomus Tertius. Officina Norstedtiana, Holmiae, 543 pp. + 1 pl." type="book" year="1855">BOHEMAN (1855)</bibRefCitation>
described this taxon from at least 
<specimenCount id="F9D0B5BFFFCCFFE7FCE0FA34FC06FA59" box="[796,952,1490,1513]" pageId="22" pageNumber="297" type="generic">two specimens</specimenCount>
as he mentioned two depositories (NHRS and collection of 
<collectingRegion id="2D12B0D4FFCCFFE7FDA8FA14FD1EF9B9" box="[596,672,1522,1545]" country="Germany" name="Bremen" pageId="22" pageNumber="297">Brême</collectingRegion>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFCCFFE7FD4CFA14FCFBF9B9" author="SPAETH" box="[688,837,1522,1545]" firstAuthor="SPAETH" pageId="22" pageNumber="297" pagination="3 - 16" refId="ref50942" refString="SPAETH F. 1912: Neue Cassiden aus Columbien, Peru, Bolivien und Ecuador. Stettiner Entomologische Zeitung 73: 3 - 16." type="journal article" year="1912">SPAETH (1912)</bibRefCitation>
transferred it to 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFCCFFE7FC0CFA14FF6FF999" authorityName="Spaeth" authorityYear="1899" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Plagiometriona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="297" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFCCFFE7FC0CFA14FF6FF999" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="297">Plagiometriona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and later, reduced its status to aberration of 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFCCFFE7FD4DF9F4FC5EF999" authority="(Boheman, 1855)" baseAuthorityName="Boheman" baseAuthorityYear="1855" box="[689,992,1554,1577]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Plagiometriona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="297" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="buqueti">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFCCFFE7FD4DF9F4FCA2F999" box="[689,796,1554,1577]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="297">P. buqueti</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFCCFFE7FCD7F9F4FC66F999" author="Boheman" box="[811,984,1554,1577]" firstAuthor="Boheman" pageId="22" pageNumber="297" refId="ref47955" refString="BOHEMAN C. H. 1855: Monographia Cassididarum. Tomus Tertius. Officina Norstedtiana, Holmiae, 543 pp. + 1 pl." type="book" year="1855">Boheman, 1855</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
without any comments (
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFCDFFE6FF10FF3AFECAFF43" author="SPAETH" box="[236,372,220,243]" firstAuthor="SPAETH" pageId="23" pageNumber="298" pagination="135 - 158" refId="ref51390" refString="SPAETH F. 1937: Neue Cassidinen des Rijksmuseums in Leiden und meiner Sammlung. Temminckia 2: 135 - 158." type="journal article" year="1937">SPAETH 1937</bibRefCitation>
). Since then, 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFCDFFE6FE02FF3AFDDEFF43" baseAuthorityName="Boheman" baseAuthorityYear="1855" box="[510,608,220,243]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Plagiometriona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="298" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bremei">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFCDFFE6FE02FF3AFDDEFF43" box="[510,608,220,243]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="298">P. bremei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was considered its junior subjective synonym (see 
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFCDFFE6FF5FFF1AFEE9FEA3" author="BOROWIEC" box="[163,343,252,275]" firstAuthor="BOROWIEC" pageId="23" pageNumber="298" refId="ref48283" refString="BOROWIEC L. 1999 a: A world catalogue of the Cassidinae (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae). Biologica Silesiae, Wroclaw, 476 pp." type="book" year="1999" yearSuffix="a">BOROWIEC 1999a</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EF697E36FFCDFFE6FF6CFEFAFC8AFEC3" blockId="23.[113,1089,220,403]" pageId="23" pageNumber="298">
I have examined 
<typeStatus id="306DC094FFCDFFE6FEBAFEFAFEC0FE83" box="[326,382,284,307]" pageId="23" pageNumber="298">types</typeStatus>
of both taxa and in my opinion they represent two distinct species and I therefore remove 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFCDFFE6FE96FEDAFE73FEE3" baseAuthorityName="Boheman" baseAuthorityYear="1855" box="[362,461,316,339]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Plagiometriona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="298" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bremei">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFCDFFE6FE96FEDAFE73FEE3" box="[362,461,316,339]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="298">P. bremei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from synonymy of 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFCDFFE6FD63FEDAFCB7FEE3" baseAuthorityName="Boheman" baseAuthorityYear="1855" box="[671,777,316,339]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Plagiometriona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="298" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="buqueti">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFCDFFE6FD63FEDAFCB7FEE3" box="[671,777,316,339]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="298">P. buqueti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and restore its species status. See 
<tableCitation id="A2544B8DFFCDFFE6FF62FEBAFF53FEC3" box="[158,237,348,371]" captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="23.[113,159,1261,1280]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="Table 1. Distinguishing characters between Plagiometriona bremei (Boheman, 1855) and P.buqueti (Boheman,1855)." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/BBA92EBEFFCDFFE6FF8DFB0BFBFCFAB0" pageId="23" pageNumber="298" tableUuid="BBA92EBEFFCDFFE6FF8DFB0BFBFCFAB0">Table 1</tableCitation>
for distinguishing characters between the two species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
